And they delivered the king’s commissions unto the king’s lieutenants and to the governors of Coelesyria and Phoenicia; and they honoured the people and the temple of God. And when these things were done, the rulers came unto me and said, The nation of Israel, the princes, the priests, and the Levites, have not put away from them the strange people of the land, nor the pollutions of the Gentiles, namely the Canaanites, Hittites, Perizzites, Jebusites, and the Moabites, Egyptians, and Edomites. For both they and their sons have married with their daughters, and the holy seed is mixed with the strange people of the land; and from the beginning of this matter the rulers and the great men have been partakers of this iniquity. And as soon as I had heard these things, I rent my clothes and my holy garment, and pulled off the hair of my head and of my beard, and sat me down sad and very heavy. Then were gathered unto me all they that were moved at the word of the Lord God of Israel, for this iniquity that was done. And I sat sad until the evening sacrifice. Then rising up from the prayer I cast myself upon the ground, and after I had found favour before the Lord, I arose and fell upon my knees, and stretched out my hands unto the Lord, and said, O Lord, I am confounded and ashamed before thy face. For our iniquities are multiplied above our heads, and our sins are gone up to heaven. From the time of our fathers until this day we have been in great sin. And for our sins and our fathers’ we with our brethren and our kings and our priests were given up to the kings of the earth, to the sword, and to captivity, and for a prey with shame. And now in some measure mercy hath been shewed unto us from thee, O Lord, that there should be left us a root and a name in the place of thy sanctuary. And now when we are come again to the light of thy law, that we might do all those things which are written in the law of the Lord, we have turned not away from our iniquities. And now, O Lord, what shall we say, having these things? For we have transgressed thy commandments, which thou gavest by the hand of thy servants the prophets, saying, The land which ye enter into to possess as an heritage is a land polluted with the pollutions of the strangers of the land, and they have filled it with their uncleanness. Therefore now shall ye not join your daughters unto their sons, neither shall ye take their daughters unto your sons. Neither shall ye seek their peace or prosperity for ever, that ye may be strong, and eat the good things of the land, and leave the inheritance of the land unto your children for ever. And all that is befallen is done unto us for our evil deeds and our great sins. For thou, O Lord, didst make our fathers as a root, and didst give us a name, as it is this day. And now we are in transgression before thee, and our sins are multiplied upon our heads. And the priests and the Levites and the rulers of the people came unto me, saying, The nation of Israel, the princes, the priests, and the Levites, have not put away from them the strange people of the land… And when these things were done, the rulers came unto me… And Esdras the priest brought the law… And the whole congregation came together… And the children of Israel were in their habitations… And they gave their hands to put away their wives…

