e me king of the whole world, and hath commanded me to build him an house at Jerusalem in Jewry. If therefore there be any of you that are of his people, let the Lord be with him, and let him go up to Jerusalem that is in Jewry, and build the house of the Lord of Israel: he is the Lord that dwelleth in Jerusalem. Whosoever therefore shall dwell in any place where he sojourneth, let his neighbours help him with gold, and with silver, With goods, and with horses, and with cattle, and with other things, besides that which they have freely offered. Then rose up the chief of the families of Juda and of the tribe of Benjamin, and the priests, and the Levites, and all they whose spirit the Lord had stirred up to go up to build the house for the Lord which is in Jerusalem. And they that dwelt round about them helped them with all manner of silver and gold, with horses and cattle, and with very many gifts, besides a great number of free offerings. And king Cyrus brought forth the vessels of the temple of the Lord, which Nebuchadnezzar had taken from Jerusalem, and had laid them up in his temple of idols. And Cyrus king of Persia brought them forth by the hand of Mithridates his treasurer, and numbered them unto Sanabassar the governor of Judea. And this was the number of them… Now when the adversaries of Judah and Benjamin heard that the children of the captivity builded the temple unto the Lord God of Israel; Then they came to Zerubbabel, and to the chief of the fathers, and said unto them, Let us build with you: for we seek your God, as ye do; and we do sacrifice unto him since the days of Esarhaddon king of Assur, which brought us up hither. But Zerubbabel, and Jeshua, and the rest of the chief of the fathers of Israel, said unto them, Ye have nothing to do with us to build an house unto our God; but we ourselves together will build unto the Lord God of Israel, as king Cyrus the king of Persia hath commanded us. Then the people of the land weakened the hands of the people