Thus the restoration of the temple, the keeping of the Passover by the returned exiles, the separation from strange wives, the reading of the law by Esdras, the great assembly and covenant renewal, the dedication with joy and offerings, the building completed under Zerubbabel and Jeshua with the help of the prophets Haggai and Zechariah, the decree of Darius confirming Cyrus’s command, the opposition overcome, the foundation laid, the vessels restored, the return from Babylon, the stirring of the spirit of Cyrus, the proclamation to rebuild the house of YHWH in Jerusalem, and the carrying away into captivity under Nebuchadnezzar, all flow backward to the glorious Passover kept by King Josiah in Jerusalem, where the priests and Levites stood in their places, the burnt offerings and sin offerings were offered according to the law, the people sang with gladness, and the feast was kept as it had not been kept since the days of Samuel the prophet — the full cycle of judgment, exile, and divine mercy returning to the zealous reform and covenant faithfulness at the beginning.
